1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:06,280
Your attention is scarce, but every day feeds, taps, and algorithms decide what gets it.

2
00:00:06,740 --> 00:00:08,280
What if you could take that control back?

3
00:00:08,780 --> 00:00:14,160
You already have the signal, your calendar, talks, messages, projects, watchlists, and

4
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,400
the assistants connected to them.

5
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,300
But most of it still comes back as more text.

6
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:22,000
And before the day even starts, nobody wants another wall of text.

7
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:24,420
Streamed text changes the format.

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:29,460
Inside the Codex app, it turns your trusted sources into a short personalized video briefing

9
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:32,840
you can actually watch, not what the algorithms want to push.

10
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,420
What you need to know.

11
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:39,640
Here is a new style explainer on the NPM Supply Chain attack built from trusted sources, ranked

12
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,940
for relevance, and delivered as a concise video.

13
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:45,900
More engaging than a summary, faster to absorb than a wall of text.

14
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:47,760
But this is bigger than news video.

15
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:53,780
Streamed text can create a daily plan, a project recap, a news digest, an architecture update,

16
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:56,960
a team handoff, or a recap from the tools you have connected.

17
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:59,940
If you can connect the tools, you can build the stream.

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:04,420
And because streamed text runs inside the Codex app, you can schedule automations to

19
00:01:04,420 --> 00:01:06,660
generate these briefings before your day starts.

20
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:11,260
So on a metro ride, you can watch what is planned for the day, what changed overnight,

21
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,520
and what your other automations already finished for you.

22
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:19,940
Instead of opening 5 apps and reading 5 summaries, you can get one briefing in a format built

23
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:20,520
for attention.

24
00:01:21,260 --> 00:01:24,800
Your sources, your ranking, your format, your stream.

25
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,000
Streamed text.

26
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,260
Watch your signal, not the algorithm.

